events.description: The ruling Liberal Democratic Party secured a two-thirds supermajority in the lower house.
A historic victory for the LDP led by Prime Minister Sanae Takaichi.

facts.fact_text: The Japanese yen fluctuated around 157 per dollar on Monday.

evidences.evidence_text: The Japanese yen fluctuated around 157 per dollar on Monday, hovering near a two-week low

facts.fact_text: Takaichi’s coalition won 352 of the 465 seats in Japan’s House of Representatives.

evidences.evidence_text: Takaichi’s coalition won 352 of the 465 seats in Japan’s House of Representatives, according to figures collated by public broadcaster NHK

facts.fact_text: The LDP alone secured a majority of 316 seats.

evidences.evidence_text: with the LDP alone securing a majority of 316

claims.claim_text: The election result gives Takaichi a mandate to pursue expansionary fiscal policies.

evidences.evidence_text: The result gives Takaichi a clear mandate from the snap election to pursue expansionary fiscal policies

claims.claim_text: Expansionary fiscal policies could further pressure the yen and Japanese government bonds.

evidences.evidence_text: a stance that could further pressure the yen and Japanese government bonds

claims.claim_text: Expansionary fiscal policies could potentially support equities.
The outcome reinforced expectations for looser fiscal policy and possible tax cuts.

evidences.evidence_text: The outcome reinforced expectations for looser fiscal policy and possible tax cuts

evidence.evidence_text: The Japanese yen fluctuated around 157 per dollar on Monday, hovering near a two-week low after the ruling Liberal Democratic Party... secured a two-thirds supermajority
a stance that could further pressure the yen and Japanese government bonds
expectations for looser fiscal policy and possible tax cuts, which have rattled Japanese financial markets in recent weeks amid concerns over Japan’s growing debt burden
